==English==
=== Pronunciation ===
*(''[[RP]]''): /ˈbɛərɪŋ/, /<tt>"bE@rIN</tt>/
*(''US''): bâr'ĭng

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

#Of a [[beam]], [[column]], or other device, carrying [[weight]] or [[load]].
#:''a '''bearing''' wall''

====Derived terms====
*[[-bearing]]

=== Noun ===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#<!--DefA-->A [[mechanical]] [[device]] that [[supports]] another part and/or reduces [[friction]]. 
#<!--DefB-->(''nautical'') The [[horizontal]] [[angle]] between the [[direction]] of an object and that of [[true north]]; subject to [[variation]] and [[deviation]] when taken by a [[magnetic]] [[compass]]
#<!--DefC-->[[relevance|Relevance]]; a relationship or connection.
#:''That has no '''bearing''' on this issue''.
#<!--DefD-->One's [[posture]], [[demeanor]], or [[manner]].
#:''She walks with a confident, self-assured '''bearing'''.''

